---
// src/pages/about-me.astro
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout sideBarActiveItemID="about-me" currentPath="/about-me">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 font-mono min-h-[85vh] flex flex-col mb-20">
    
    <!-- Page Header -->
    <div class="mt-12 mb-10 boot-sequence" style="--delay: 0ms;">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-primary mb-2 flex items-center">
        ./whoami.sh<span id="main-cursor" class="ml-1 inline-block w-3 h-8 bg-primary"></span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg opacity-80 text-secondary">The human behind the keyboard.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 1: The Origin Story -->
    <div class="border border-neutral bg-[#0a0a0a] mb-8 text-sm shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(34,211,238,0.05)] stdout-container">
      <div class="bg-neutral/40 px-3 py-1.5 text-xs text-base-content/50 border-b border-neutral flex items-center">
        <div class="flex space-x-1.5 mr-3">
          <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#FF5F56]"></div>
          <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#FFBD2E]"></div>
          <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#27C93F]"></div>
        </div>
        <span>cat origin_story.md</span>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 md:p-8">
        <p class="opacity-90 leading-relaxed text-base-content mb-5">
          <span class="text-accent font-bold mr-2 terminal-prompt">guest@haiqal:~#</span>
          <span class="stdout-line">School gave me the basics, but let's be real—my actual learning always happens outside the classroom.</span>
        </p>
        <p class="opacity-90 leading-relaxed text-base-content mb-5 stdout-line">
          For me, it's always been about building personal stuff and making fun projects that I actually care about. Instead of just doing assignments, I end up learning the most from scrolling tech social media, reading random documentation, and lately, getting insanely efficient by learning alongside AI.
        </p>
        <p class="opacity-90 leading-relaxed text-base-content stdout-line">
          > <span class="text-accent font-bold">Lowkey do not know how i managed to do it last time wihout AI, just rawdog documentation and stackoverflow</span>
        </p>
        <p class="opacity-90 leading-relaxed text-base-content mt-5 stdout-line">
          Special shoutout to my mentor and coach, <a href="https://github.com/FayRd" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-secondary hover:text-secondary/80 underline decoration-secondary/30 underline-offset-2 transition-all">FayRd</a>, who guided me through full-stack development. He's a phenomenal network engineer who taught me optimization, server administration, and how to push system and hardware-level performance to its absolute limits.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 2: Current Workflow -->
    <div class="border border-neutral bg-[#0a0a0a] mb-8 text-sm shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(34,211,238,0.05)] stdout-container">
      <div class="bg-neutral/40 px-3 py-1.5 text-xs text-base-content/50 border-b border-neutral flex items-center">
        <div class="flex space-x-1.5 mr-3">
          <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#FF5F56]"></div>
          <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#FFBD2E]"></div>
          <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#27C93F]"></div>
        </div>
        <span>cat workflow.yml</span>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 md:p-8">
        <p class="opacity-90 leading-relaxed text-base-content mb-5">
          <span class="text-accent font-bold mr-2 terminal-prompt">guest@haiqal:~#</span>
          <span class="stdout-line">To build full-stack stuff solo without burning out, I've had to adapt.</span>
        </p>
        <p class="opacity-90 leading-relaxed text-base-content mb-5 stdout-line">
          Ngl, I rarely write boilerplate from scratch anymore. AI does the heavy lifting for the boring syntax, which lets me vibe with the actual fun parts—like figuring out how the database should look, connecting the dots, and making sure it doesn't break when deployed.
        </p>
        <p class="opacity-90 leading-relaxed text-success/90 stdout-line font-bold">
          > Status: Less "typing every line", more "vibing with AI, prompting, and fixing its hallucinations."
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 3: Engineering Philosophy -->
    <div class="border border-neutral bg-[#0a0a0a] mb-8 text-sm shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(34,211,238,0.05)] stdout-container">
      <div class="bg-neutral/40 px-3 py-1.5 text-xs text-base-content/50 border-b border-neutral flex items-center">
        <div class="flex space-x-1.5 mr-3">
          <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#FF5F56]"></div>
          <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#FFBD2E]"></div>
          <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#27C93F]"></div>
        </div>
        <span>cat philosophy.txt</span>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 md:p-8">
        <p class="opacity-90 leading-relaxed text-base-content mb-5">
          <span class="text-accent font-bold mr-2 terminal-prompt">guest@haiqal:~#</span>
          <span class="stdout-line">Two things are true: Laravel is lowkey goated, and I am definitely not a designer.</span>
        </p>
        <p class="opacity-90 leading-relaxed text-base-content mb-5 stdout-line">
          Taking UI/UX classes basically just proved that I shouldn't be trusted to make a logo from scratch lol. I can definitely replicate a Figma design, but my brain is just wired to think about the backend and how things actually work under the hood.
        </p>
        <p class="opacity-90 leading-relaxed text-base-content stdout-line">
          Laravel has been my go-to because it honestly feels like a cheat code for APIs. Hook that up to my homelab, and I'm just living my best life experimenting with servers.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
<!-- Section 4: Offline -->
    <div class="border border-neutral bg-[#0a0a0a] mb-8 text-sm shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(34,211,238,0.05)] stdout-container">
      <div class="bg-neutral/40 px-3 py-1.5 text-xs text-base-content/50 border-b border-neutral flex items-center">
        <div class="flex space-x-1.5 mr-3">
          <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#FF5F56]"></div>
          <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#FFBD2E]"></div>
          <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#27C93F]"></div>
        </div>
        <span>whoami --offline</span>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 md:p-8">
        <p class="opacity-90 leading-relaxed text-base-content mb-5">
          <span class="text-accent font-bold mr-2 terminal-prompt">guest@haiqal:~#</span>
          <span class="stdout-line">When I'm away from the keyboard...</span>
        </p>
        
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
          <div class="opacity-90 leading-relaxed text-base-content stdout-line">
            <span class="text-primary font-bold">Status:</span> Upgrading the homelab
          </div>
          <div class="opacity-90 leading-relaxed text-base-content stdout-line">
            <span class="text-primary font-bold">Hardware:</span> Salvaged office workstations
          </div>
          <div class="opacity-90 leading-relaxed text-base-content stdout-line">
            <span class="text-primary font-bold">Hobbies:</span> ["pc_part_hunting", "homelab_window_shopping", "home_appliance_shopping", "anime_&_manga", "gaming"]
          </div>
          <div class="opacity-90 leading-relaxed text-base-content stdout-line">
            <span class="text-primary font-bold">Side_Quests:</span> Salvaging hardware, <a href="/nino" class="hover:text-[#ff80bf] hover:bg-[#ff80bf]/10 transition-colors duration-300 rounded px-1 cursor-pointer" title="Execute classified payload">Nino</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', () => {
    // Terminal stdout Gen Animation Logic
    const stdoutObserver = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
      entries.forEach(entry => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting && !entry.target.classList.contains('executed')) {
          entry.target.classList.add('executed'); 
          
          const lines = entry.target.querySelectorAll('.stdout-line');
          let delay = 0;
          
          lines.forEach((line, index) => {
            setTimeout(() => {
              if (index > 0) lines[index - 1].classList.remove('printing');
              line.classList.add('printed', 'printing');
              
              if (index === lines.length - 1) {
                setTimeout(() => {
                  line.classList.remove('printing');
                  line.classList.add('finished'); 
                }, 800);
              }
            }, delay);
            // Randomize typing speed for realism
            delay += Math.floor(Math.random() * 90) + 30; 
          });
        }
      });
    }, { rootMargin: "0px 0px -10% 0px" });

    document.querySelectorAll('.stdout-container').forEach(container => {
      stdoutObserver.observe(container);
    });
  });
</script>

<style>
  /* Standard terminal blink */
  @keyframes terminal-blink {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
    50% { opacity: 0; }
  }

  #main-cursor {
    animation: terminal-blink 1s step-end infinite;
  }

  .boot-sequence {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(10px);
    animation: fade-up 0.6s ease-out forwards;
    animation-delay: var(--delay);
  }
  @keyframes fade-up {
    to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }

  /* --- Terminal Execution Styles --- */
  .stdout-container:not(.executed) .terminal-prompt::after {
    content: '█';
    display: inline-block;
    margin-left: 8px;
    color: currentColor;
    animation: terminal-blink 1s step-end infinite;
    vertical-align: baseline;
  }

  .stdout-line {
    opacity: 0;
    visibility: hidden;
  }
  
  .stdout-line.printed {
    opacity: 1;
    visibility: visible;
  }
  
  .stdout-line.printing::after {
    content: '█';
    display: inline-block;
    margin-left: 6px;
    color: currentColor;
    vertical-align: baseline;
  }

  .stdout-line.finished::after {
    content: '█';
    display: inline-block;
    margin-left: 6px;
    color: currentColor;
    animation: terminal-blink 1s step-end infinite;
    vertical-align: baseline;
  }
</style>